	Generating Leads
	Linear Regression		the best fit line through all data points
	Logistic Regression		the adoption for linear regression to problems of classification
	Decision Trees			a graph that uses branching method to match all possible outcome of a decision
	Random Forest			it takes the average of many decision trees. Each tree is weaker than the full decision tree, but combining them we get better overall performance
	Gradient Boosting Machines	it uses even weaker decision trees that increasingly focused on 'hard examples'
	K-Nearest Neighnors
	K-Means Clustering
	Naive Bayes
	Support Vector Machines
	Neural Networks			mimics, the behaviour of the brain. NNs are interconnected Neurons that pass messages to each other.
					Deep Learning uses several layers of NNs to put one after the other.


